Quote: The Totara Flat Races are the chief topic up the Grey Valley at present. The smiddy at the Flat is the scene of a great many horsey [sic] operations, the patching up of some old pretender that never won the Sydney Gold Cup or any other, is the work of nearly every hour of the day.
